nodes.title: Update Log v4
widgets_values:
- Better Crash Handling: Images are re-batched which prevent overloading crashes while exporting Masks and SoftEdgePlus pass. 

- Input Path Video: Now no need to remove the quotes from the path, it will remove itself. You can enter with or without quotes both acceptable. 

- Lower Ram Consumption when queuing first time: It took a lot of CPU ram when running for the first time in v3, now it should be lower.   

- Re-visited and Organized All Nodes.

- Image Saving is much Faster now

nodes.title: Usage Tips
widgets_values:
Videos with these characteristics will perform best with these passes (Pick any 2): 

1) For Face Closeups - Line Art | soft edge | Face Only Open Pose with Soft Edge Plus|  
2) For Half Body Shots - Use Line Art with Soft edge/Plus or Open Pose. 
3) For Full body shots - Use Open Pose with line Art or Soft edge/Plus
4) For Architecture or landscape - Use Depth with Soft edge, line art or Canny. 
5) For Flat Logos, or Typos - Use Normal with Line Art, Soft edge/Plus.


Check if open pose passes, are all over the place jumping around, jittering markers, or cannot find important body markers, then avoid the open pose pass. 

Two Control net passes are enough to make a good Render. You can experiment with any combination from the above.

nodes.title: 1) ControlNet Passes Exporter v4.0
widgets_values:
Instruction:

1) Copy as Path - Right Click on your Video inside explorer and click copy as path and paste it inside the Input Video Path node. 

2) Copy Output Folder Address - Copy the address of the folder you want to save the Passes and paste it in the Output path node. It should NOT be in quotes. Eg: F:\Test 

3) Select the Passes you want to extract. Enable = 1, Disable = 0. Edit their properties if you want.


4) [Optional] If you have a high-resolution video like 4k, you might want to downscale it to 1k to get optimal results for rendering. Enter multiplier in "scale_by" input. 

5) You can also limit the resolution size and fit inside your defined limit using the fit scale node. The max value of either height or width. 

6) [optional] You can also custom resize it. Enable it by entering value as 1 and use custom dimensions.

7) Save Source Images is enabled by default for original reference, lip sync or sequencing. 

-----------
Note: 

*Disable the already rendered pass if you are using this again from zero for another pass else it will make 2x images. Decide firsthand which 2 passes you want. There are chances you can mess up the image sequence. 

*If you want to use this again for another pass, you can use it easily again, the extra black image goes into trash folder which does not disturb the main image sequence or numbering.

*Open Pose resolution is set to image resolution by default from v3 

----------

This Workflow Extract ControlNet Passes before main render to save time in testing animation.

I post all documented workflows on my patreon for free Link: patreon.com/jerrydavos

nodes.title: 1) Input Video - Automatic
widgets_values:
Lap Counter: This is the new Feature; it increases the skip frames after every queue automatically according to the batch range set by you. 
1) Enter Batch Range and Enable the Passes.  
2) After the first run it will tell the number n of queues you need in the Neon Green Node.
3) Press the Queue Prompt Button n times till your Queue Size = N in the side menu. 

It will automatically stop if you by mistakenly entered more laps, with no images found error, which is fine, no need to worry.  

*IMP: N is the total Laps need. Before starting for final render make sure to set the Lap Counter to 0. 


Batch Range: Specify how much frames your pc can handle in one go. (eg: 200 Images for 1280x720 size is safe for 8GB vram, 100 frames for 1920x1080). If your save node crashes use lower. 

**IMP: CPU RAM is also important, if you have lower than 32 GB Extract 1-2 Passes at a time only and 10-20 Batch Range. All Images from all enabled passes get loaded in CPU Ram, may encounter choking or CPU ram. Use Higer values Carefully... Use Auto Feature to avoid this choking. 

____________________________________________________________________

How to use Example: 

If you have a 20 second video of 1280x720 with 30 fps then your total frames will be 30x30 = 600 frames which will be shown in the total frames node.

First Queue - Batch Range - 200 | Lap Counter - 0 | Queue Prompt N Times: Null

After First Queue N times value will change from null to 3 so I will press Queue prompt 2 more times until the "Queue Size" in the side menu above queue prompt button, reaches value N. 

The frames will be rendered automatically now, no need to set the skip frames manually again and again.     
_________________________________________________________________

Enabling All Passes may crash your Comfyui. Use 4 Maximum to be safe, watch your CPU Ram.

nodes.title: Batch Range and Skip Frames - Manual
widgets_values:
*Unmute the Input Video Manual Group if you want to use manual image loading. Connect the Reroute to the Upscale/Downscale node and use as normal. 


When exporting for longer videos or HD videos, the save node crashes will crash due to ram overloading, use around 50 or below in batch range. 

Batch Range: Specify how much frames your pc can handle in one go. Use 50 or below for safe render. 

Skip Frames: After Every Batch skip the total rendered frames.  

____________________________________________________________________

How to use Example: 

If you have a 30 second video of 1280x720 with 30 fps then your total frames will be 30x30 = 900 frames
Then 

Batch 1: Range - 400 | Skip Frames - 0
Batch 2: Range - 400 | Skip Frames - 400
Batch 3: Range - 100 | Skip Frames - 800

Total rendered frames: 900

nodes.title: Batch Range Important Note
widgets_values: Do NOT put 0 in Batch Range to Prevent Crashing

nodes.title: Lap Counter Important Note
widgets_values: Make Sure to Put 0 in the Lap Counter before Starting for Final Render.

nodes.title: Automatic Lite
widgets_values:
Lap Counter: This is the new Feature; it increases the skip frames after every queue automatically according to the batch range set by you. 

1) Enter Batch Range and Enable the Passes.  
2) Click Extras Option > Auto Queue Button on the side menu and select "changed" and then Queue Prompt, it will run automatically and then stop when it has done all the frames. 


*Set Batch Range 50 if you have high CPU Ram >= 32 GB
*Set Batch Range 10 if you have low CPU Ram < 32 GB

This Lite version will be effective to save time and prevent memory spike.  

Set the Lap Counter to "Increment" to enable auto skipping feature.
